A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Kenneth Rogers Bridges; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Kenneth Rogers Bridges has captured and preserved the rich history and culture
3 of rural Georgia in the 1940s through his vivid storytelling, allowing readers to experience
4 firsthand the values, struggles, and experiences of that era; and
5 WHEREAS, he writes with a deep appreciation for his early years of financial hardship,
6 shaped by the love of a caring family who instilled in him the importance of hard work,
7 education, and moral values; and
8 WHEREAS, his literary talent enables him to share his memories in a way that draws readers
9 into his colorful narratives, ensuring that the stories of a vanishing time remain alive for
10 future generations; and
11 WHEREAS, Kenneth Rogers Bridges holds both a bachelor's and a master's degree in
12 vocational agriculture from the University of Georgia, and he has dedicated his career to
13 teaching the subject at several Georgia schools; and
