14 WHEREAS, he has further served as chairman of the Board of Education for Oconee
15 County, chairman of farm services for Jackson County, and as a member of numerous
16 educational and agricultural boards and committees; and
17 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentleman has given inspiration to many through his high
18 ideals, morals, and deep concern for his fellow citizens, and he possesses the vast wisdom
19 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
20 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
21 WHEREAS, Kenneth Rogers Bridges is a person of magnanimous strengths with an
22 unimpeachable reputation for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
24 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body recognize and commend Kenneth Rogers Bridges for his many
27 outstanding contributions to North Georgia and extend the most sincere best wishes for
28 continued health and happiness.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
31 Kenneth Rogers Bridges.
